==Other sports== [[Military sports]] were held at the games, reflecting the [[militarism]] of Nazi and fascist states.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Teja|first1=Angela |last2=Arnaud|first2=Pierre |last3=Riordan|first3=James |title=Sport and International Politics |year=2003|publisher=E & FN SPON|isbn=0-203-47658-1 |origyear=1998|page=147|chapter=Italian sport and international relations under fascism}}</ref> Other sports included [[tennis]], [[boxing]], [[field hockey]] (Germany beat two Italian teams<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lisa.gerda-henkel-stiftung.de/binaries/navigation/5913/file_45_1937_1939fuerpdf.doc?t=1446553566&usg=AFQjCNEJU8e9UaiwecGM_UYHO0vy50FGIQ&sig2=Vf74J3cjMz7nB-ByjbSU8A |format=[[MS Word]] |title=Deutscher Hockeysport 1937-1939: Vergessene Aspekte der deutschen Sportgeschichte? |last=Happ|first=Martin|work=LISA|publisher=Gerda Henkel Stiftung|language=German|accessdate=22 May 2016|location=Düsseldorf}}</ref>), [[basketball]], [[swimming (sport)|swimming]], [[handball]], [[association football]], [[rugby football|rugby]], [[rowing (sport)|rowing]], [[fencing]], [[gliding]], and [[water polo]] (won by Hungary<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fisu.net/en/A-University-Athlete-like-No-Other-3133.html?mbID=6579|title=A University Athlete like No Other|date=28 August 2015|publisher=[[International University Sports Federation]]|accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref>).<ref name="poster">{{cite web |url=http://content.cdlib.org/ark:/28722/bk0007t746g/?layout=metadata |title=Studenten-Weltspiele, Wien 20.-27. August 1939 |work=German Nazi posters from the Second World War era |publisher=[[UC Berkeley]], [[Bancroft Library]] |accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref>
